  "prompt_text": "A chess board has 64 squares. Two opposite corners are removed. Can you cover the remaining 62 squares with dominoes that each cover exactly 2 adjacent squares? Prove your answer.",
  "response_text": "To determine if it is possible to cover the remaining 62 squares of a chessboard with 31 dominoes after removing two opposite corners, we need to analyze the properties of the chessboard and the dominoes.\n\n### Analysis\n\n1. **Initial Setup**:\n   - A standard chessboard consists of 8 rows and 8 columns, making a total of 64 squares.\n   - Each domino covers exactly 2 adjacent squares.\n\n2. **Coloring the Chessboard**:\n   - The chessboard is typically colored in a checkerboard pattern, with alternating black and white squares.\n   - There are 32 black squares and 32 white squares on a full chessboard.\n\n3. **Effect of Removing Two Opposite Corners**:\n   - Let's assume the removed corners are both black (or both white). This assumption doesn't affect the logic, as the problem would be symmetrically equivalent for opposite colors.\n   - Removing two black squares leaves 30 black squares and 32 white squares.\n\n4. **Domino Coverage**:\n   - Each domino must cover one black square and one white square.\n   - To completely cover the board with 31 dominoes, there must be an equal number of black and white squares available to be paired up.\n\n5. **Conclusion**:\n   - With 30 black squares and 32 white squares remaining, it is impossible to pair every black square with a white square using dominoes because there are always 2 more white squares than black squares.\n\nTherefore, it is not possible to cover the remaining 62 squares of the chessboard with 31 dominoes after removing two opposite corners.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 7\nG (Goal Directedness): 8\nP (Pattern Recognition): 9\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 8\nY (Affective Modeling): 7\nF (Flexibility): 6\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
